{
  "text": "Several other potential pathways for the formation of performic acid were considered in the literature, although more definitive conclusions would require detailed modeling studies. For example, Curran et al. [CITATION_1] have included reaction (R16) in their models and, with a subsequent recombination of ȮCHO with OH, performic acid could be formed. However, the authors suggest this recombination to be only a minor channel, as (R16) competes with an internal H atom transfer via a five-center transition state and subsequent dissociatioṅ",
